istribution designed to take PRNG values as input.The random library has many random numbers distributions, most of which you will never use unless you’re doing some kind of statistical analysis. But there’s one random number distribution that’s extremely useful: auniform distributionis a random number distribution that produces outputs between two numbers X and Y (inclusive) with equal probability.Here’s a similar program to the one above, using a uniform distribution to simulate the roll of a 6-sided dice:#include <iostream>
